snippet.textDisplay:
Did ya'll knew that in Russia we actually call the dish itself the hotdog, but the meat in it -- sausage (never hotdog).
And what you call sausage we call... errr... imagime a small salami... then imagine you don't think that a small salami is weird and you have a name for it. That word is how russians would call american sausage!
It provides great deal of confusion when I have to translate stuff =)
